<html><head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>TOEIC Results</title></head><body><h1>TOEIC SPEAKING RESULTS</h1><h3>Part 3: Weather (Q6) (ID: 99)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What do you usually do on rainy days?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> On the rainy days, i often stay at home, watch the rain next to the windows. I also turn on the music and enjoy it !.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Health (Q4) (ID: 100)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What do you do to stay healthy?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> To stay healthy, i have a good eating habbit. 
VD: I eat more vegetable and restrict fast food, drink enough water per day.
-> I do excercise. I spend 30 minutues per day to practise.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Health (Q5) (ID: 101)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">How often do you exercise?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> Often do at the weekend. From Monday and Friday, i am busy with personal work. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Health (Q6) (ID: 102)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think people today care enough about their health?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Not entirely. 
-> A lot of people are careful with taking of their health
-> But other people, especially younger generation, they often eat fast food, stay up late and they seldom go outside or do excercise. Because they too focus on the Internet, work, they have less time to take care of themselves.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Technology (Q4) (ID: 103)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What electronic device do you use the most?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> I think it is the mobile phone. What do you use it for ?.
At work, i use smartphone to connect with collegue and look for information on the Internet or note down the tasks. 
At home, I use mobile phone for entertainment (giải trí), for example; chat and make phone call with friends and parents, listen to music, .watch films, surf webs, ..</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Technology (Q5) (ID: 104)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">How has technology changed your daily life?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> It changed a lot in many aspects for example, 
1. In the past, we just read books on papers but now we can read e-books on the Internet for free anywhere at anytime with a phone. 
2. A long time ago, if you wanted to meet other people, you had to meet face-to-face but now thanks to the Internet, we can make a phone call. This can save a lot of time moving,
 </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Technology (Q6) (ID: 105)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think we rely too much on technology?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Yes, i agree with that. 
I think til now, i have a bad habbit. At the morning, when i wake up i have to check on my phone for news. During the meal, i always surf webs on the mobile phone while eating. When i move on the street, i always use google maps to check the locations and i do not remmeber the route.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Learning (Q5) (ID: 110)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you prefer studying in a library or at home?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> I think i prefer stuyding at home. Because at home, it is very quite and private to learn. I do not have to move. It save a lot of time. I do not have to buy monthly subscription. It save a lot of money. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Learning (Q6) (ID: 111)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What is the best way to learn a new skill?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> It is to practise more. From mistakes, people learn new lessons, new ways to solve the problems. So the important thing is to be more confidient and try more. It will extend your experiences. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Clothes (Q4) (ID: 112)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What kind of clothes do you usually wear?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> At work -> I always wear basic clothes: A shirt or short dress. because it is formal and it is suitable for dress code. 
-> At home -> I usally wear comfortable clothes because i do not meet anyone so it is enjoyable.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Clothes (Q5) (ID: 113)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you follow fashion trends?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> I do not follow fashion trend.(khong ton tien,thoi gian).
+) I just wear basic clothes because it saves money and i do not have to spend time to choose clothes. 
1. The clothes show a lot about us, it tell one character.  Introvert person, they always wear dark colour, but with fashionable person, they wear trendy clothes, it means they are flexiable
2. Trendy clothes is pretty expensive. It shows their social positions (status). 

</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Clothes (Q6) (ID: 114)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think clothes reflect a person's personality?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Do you think clothes reflect a person's personality?
Yes, i agree with that.
With instrovert person  they always wear black colour. they do not want  attention, while extrovert person, wear colourful clothes because they want to hightlight themshelves from the crowd. 
While, people who wear trendy clothes, they are flexible.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Hobbies (Q6) (ID: 123)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think having a hobby is important? Why?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Not entirely. 
Some people have good hobby. for example, people who enjoy reading books, it helps them to extend their knowledge. 
While, there are some bad hobby. like smoking. It is not good for their health and people arround them. I think they should change this hobby. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Daily Routine (Q4) (ID: 124)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What is the first thing you do in the morning?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> I often take a look at my mobile for any new messages. I think it is a bad habbit. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Daily Routine (Q5) (ID: 125)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What is your favorite part of the day?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> I think it is at the end of my working hours. Because after all, i really hope to return back my home. I can turn off the computer, allow my eyes and mind to rest. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Daily Routine (Q6) (ID: 126)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you prefer to wake up early or stay up late?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> I prefer to stay up late. Because i only stay up late if the next day is occassion or a day off.</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Television (Q4) (ID: 127)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">How often do you watch TV?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> In the past, i watched TV everyday, but til now i seldom watch TV because now i can watch movies on my mobile phone. It is more convinient, i can watch films on phone while lying on the bed. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Television (Q5) (ID: 128)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What is your favorite TV show?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Recently i have watched a programe it named Ton Hoa Sen. it is a charity programme where a lot of poor people join in, if they win, they can receive a lot of money. This will help them to overcome difficult situations. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Television (Q6) (ID: 129)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think TV is good for children?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Not entirely.
-> With educational programme on TV, the children can learn lessons from it. 
-> But now, there are many violence programes on TV, it is not good for children if they copy it.
</p><hr><h3>Part 3: Pets (Q4) (ID: 130)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you have any pets?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> I do not have pets. because it is messy and dirty and if i have a pet, i have to take responsibilites for it: take care of it,buy foods, bring it to the hospital, ... it is waste of time and money. 
Do you grow any vegetable ?.
 I do not grow any vegetable, because i know taking care of something is demanding.  i have to take responsibilites for it: take care of it,buy foods, bring it to the hospital, ... it is waste of time and money. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Pets (Q5) (ID: 131)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What is a popular pet in your country?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Dogs and cats are one of the most famous pet in my country. 
1. It is affordable (đủ tiền để mua). It is only 1 million per cub.
2. It is easy to take care of. 
3. They brings many benefits for owner VD: dog can protect their house, cat can catch mice. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: Pets (Q6) (ID: 132)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you think pets are good companions?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Not entirely.
Some pets are friendly. They will be loyal. For exmaple, Dog and cats are one of the most famous pets in VietNam. they share a good companions with owners. It can be a memeber of owner family.
But some pets are dangerous. like snakes, scorpions, ...</p><hr><h3>Part 3: City Life (Q4) (ID: 133)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">Do you enjoy living in the city?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Not entirely. It is two-sided
On the positive side. 1. convinient. -> look for jobs, have more chances for personal develop, have high life quality like better education and healthcare system. you can always find what you need
On the negative side. 2. lifetyle is very fast (people seldom do excerices and often eat fast food, traffic are crowded), environment is polluted.


</p><hr><h3>Part 3: City Life (Q5) (ID: 134)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What are the advantages of living in a big city?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> -> 1. convinient. It has many buildings -> ___->  
-> 2. job opportunities -> personal development
-> 3. high life quality -> better education and healthcare system. </p><hr><h3>Part 3: City Life (Q6) (ID: 135)</h3><p><div class="bg-white p-4 border rounded shadow-sm text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-slate-700">What are the disadvantages of city life?</div></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> 1. traffic jams -> take more time to move
2. lifestyle -> fast -> people seldom do excericise and eat more fast food
3. environment is polluted -> it is not good citizen health.
</p><hr></body></html>